te%20their%20victims'%20organs%20at%20Ogolobyak's%20apartment%2C%20according%20to%20court%20document%20cited%20by%20Russian%20outlet%20%3Cem%3E76.ru%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20cult%20was%20named%20%26quot%3BHitler%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20court%20documents%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20in%20February%20last%20year%2C%20Russia%20has%20been%20recruiting%20extensively%20from%20prisons%20to%20assist%20its%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOgolobyak's%20father%20told%20the%20Russian%20news%20outlet%20that%20the%2033-year-old%20served%20with%20Russia's%20%26quot%3BStorm%20Z%26quot%3B%20unit%20and%20is%20now%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20true.%20He%20served%20there%20for%20six%20months%20in%20Storm%20Z.%20After%20being%20wounded%2C%20he%20is%20disabled.%20He%20is%20walking%2C%20but%20the%20wound%20was%20serious%2C%26quot%3B%20Ogolobyak's%20father%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20is%20unlikely%20that%20he%20will%20be%20sent%20to%20fight%20in%20Ukraine%20again%20due%20to%20his%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOgolobyak%20was%20meant%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20prison%20until%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20trial%2C%20he%20was%20described%20by%20prosecutors%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bwarrior%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20group.%20The%20prosecutors%20said%20his%20victims%20included%20a%20young%20couple%20who%20were%20brutally%20attacked.%20Prosecutors%20claimed%20that%20Ogolobyak%20%26quot%3Bcounted%20the%20blows%20out%20loud%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20man%20was%20killed.%20%26quot%3BHe%20counted%20until%20he%20hit%20666%2C%26quot%3B%20prosecutor%20Yelena%20Smirnova%20was%20quoted%20saying%20by%20%3Cem%3E76.ru%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20number%20of%20pardoned%20convicts%20have%20been%20reported%20to%20have%20committed%20new%20crimes%20after%20returning%20from%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20leading%20prisoner's%20rights%20activist%20Olga%20Roma