3E%3Cstrong%3EPreparing%20amid%20uncertainty%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGreg%2C%20who%20works%20in%20technology%20for%20a%20large%20bank%20in%20Connecticut%2C%20is%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20HENRY%20spectrum.%20He's%20in%20his%20mid-40s%2C%20has%20already%20saved%20%241.5%20million%20for%20retirement%2C%20and%20has%20a%20combined%20income%20of%20around%20%24300%2C000%20with%20his%20wife.%20Still%2C%20Greg%20%E2%80%94%20who%20asked%20to%20use%20just%20his%20first%20name%20for%20privacy%20concerns%20%E2%80%94%20acknowledges%20he's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fsigns-saving-too-much-for-retirement-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoversaving%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20is%20somewhat%20paranoid%20about%20the%20economy%20and%20technological%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20wealthier%20than%20many%20HENRYs%2C%20Greg%20still%20doesn't%20feel%20rich.%20His%20mortgage%20is%20%241%2C400%20a%20month%2C%20he%20bought%20a%20truck%20after%20his%2017-year-old%20car%20fell%20apart%2C%20and%20he%20reduced%20spending%20on%20non-essentials.%20He's%20planning%20for%20an%20%24800%2C000%20retirement%20home%2C%20though%20he's%20worried%20that%20tech-heavy%20industries%20like%20finance%20and%20insurance%20could%20be%20at%20risk%20as%20AI%20becomes%20more%20prevalent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20we%20might%20technically%20be%20over-saving%20is%20that%20we%20have%20no%20idea%20what%20healthcare%20costs%20are%20going%20to%20look%20like%20when%20we%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20Greg%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-social-security%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we're%20definitely%20not%20counting%20on%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20this%2060%25%20rate%20of%20savings%20stems%20from%20years%20of%20trying%20to%20get%20out%20of%20debt%20with%20his%20wife.%20He%20said%20his%20ne