0Oxford%20Economics.%20The%20result%20is%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented%20unaffordability%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoffat%20is%20concerned%20that%20as%20affordability%20crisis%20continues%20and%20immigration%20rates%20remain%20high%2C%20Canadians%20will%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fcanada%2Fbritish-columbia%2Fhousing-crisis-immigration-1.6878540%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblame%20high%20prices%20on%20immigration%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20seek%20to%20limit%20migration.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bnnbloomberg.ca%2Fmost-canadians-see-immigration-increase-as-negative-for-housing-costs-1.1956429%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERecent%20polling%20has%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20growing%20share%20of%20Canadians%20feel%20this%20way%2C%20threatening%20the%20government's%20liberal%20stance%20on%20immigration%20policy.%20But%20immigration%20is%20just%20one%20of%20many%20factors%20at%20play%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0Canada's%20housing%20crisis%20far%20preceded%20the%20rise%20in%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20starting%20to%20cause%20backlash%20here%2C%20you're%20starting%20to%20see%20anti-immigration%20sentiment%2C%26quot%3B%20Moffat%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20unless%20things%20get%20dramatically%20worse%20in%20Canada%2C%20economists%20say%20American%20policymakers%20won't%20be%20spooked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20market%20doesn't%20collapse%2C%20then%20America%20junior%20just%20kind%20of%20remains%20an%20interesting%20story%2C%20but%20not%20a%20policy%20lesson%2C%26quot%3B%20Lander%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEconomists%20aren't%20predicting%20a%20repeat%20of%20the%20American%20housing%20market%20collapse%20of%202008%20in%20Canada.%20The%20Canadian%20banking%20sector%20is%20more%20closely%20regulated%20than%20the%20US's.%20A%20handful%20of%20major%20banks%20dominate%20residential%20mortgages%2C%20so%20there's%20less%20competition%20and%20therefore%20less%20risky%20behavior%20than%20was%20common%20in%20the%20early-aughts%20US%20housing%20bubble%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhen%20it%20comes%20to%20lending%2C%20Lander%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20mortgage%20rates%20so%20high%2C%20home%20sales%20have%20declined%20recently.%20In%20October%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fcanadian-home-sales-fall-56-october-2023-11-15%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20sales%20fell%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A05.6%25.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20home%20prices%20overall%20have%20flattened%20somewhat.%20Stillo%20believes%20Canada's%20housing%20bubble%20has%20been%20slowly%20%26quot%3Bdeflating%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20last%2018%20months%2C%20despite%20an%20upswing%20in%20prices%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20disorderly%20bursting%2C%20but%20definitely%20deflating%2C%20in%20my%20opinion%2C%20since%20the%20spring%20of%202022%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20mortgage%20rates%20soaring%20last%20year%2C%20US%20housing%20prices%20only%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Feconomy%2Fhousing%2Fthe-fall-in-home-prices-may-already-be-over-3496d6bb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebriefly%20declined%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20about%20five%20months%20before%20resuming%20their%20rise.%20This%20is%20in%20part%20because%20of%20the%20US's%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20which%20discourage%20those%20with%20low%20rates%20to%20sell%20their%20homes%20and%20sign%20up%20for%20today's%20much%20higher%20rates%20with%20a%20new%20home.%20This%20leads%20to%20low%20inventory%2C%20exacerbating%20supply%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20is%20so%20desperate%20that%20many%20Canadians%20are%20celebrating%20the%20drop%20in%20prices.%20Seventy%20percent%20of%20respondents%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnanos.co%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F2023-2452-Bloomberg-August-Populated-report-with-tabulations.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20Nanos%20Research%2FBloomberg%20News%20poll%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20they%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bhappy%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%20happy%26quot%3B%20if%20home%20values%20declined.%20This%20is%20despite%20the%20fact%20two-thirds%20of%20Canadian%20households%20own%20their%20homes%20and%20could%20see%20housing%20equity%20drop%20alongside%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20isn't%20consensus%20on%20if%20and%20when%20Canada's%20housing%20bubble%20will%20burst%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%20even%20if%20there%20is%20a%20bubble.%20Lander%20says%20there's%20no%20end%20in%20sight.%20While%20housing%20prices%20have%20flattened%20recently%20as%20demand%20softens%2C%20he%20says%20they%20show%20no%20sign%20of%20significantly%20declining.%20When%20the%20Canadian%20central%20bank%20lowers%20interest%20rates%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20as%20the%20recession%20deepens%2C%20that'll%20only%20juice%20demand%20for%20homes%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20if%20housing%20prices%20come%20down%2C%20it's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20towards%20anything%20reflecting%20market%20value%20%E2%80%94%20that%20bubble%20will%20still%20be%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Lander%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20market%20hasn't%20imploded%20when%20interest%20rates%20are%20at%20a%2025-year%20high%2C%20when%20those%20rates%20start%20coming%20down%2C%20the%20market%20is%20going%20to%20take%20off%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoffat%20doesn't%20think%20Canada%20has%20a%20housing%20bubble%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0he%20predicts%20that%20while%20prices%20are%20and%20will%20be%20volatile%2C%20they'll%20continue%20rising%20because%20the%20country%20simply%20doesn't%20have%20enough%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Americans%2C%20Canadians%20are%20increasingly%20worried%20about%20housing%20costs.%20They%20list%20inflation%20as%20their%20top%20concern%2C%20closely%20followed%20by%20housing%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ctvnews.ca%2Fcanada%2Fconcerns-over-housing-environment-take-different-turns-as-canadians-feel-fin