%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20be%20likable%20during%20your%20company%20holiday%20party%20or%20family%20dinner%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Stanford%20lecturer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221863%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Matt%20Abrahams%20headshot%20in%20a%20blue%20sweater%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655d04e99c7d23cb3b9e4b2c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221863%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMatt%20Abrahams%20is%20a%20lecturer%20at%20Stanford's%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business.%3Cp%3ENancy%20Rothstein%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMatt%20Abrahams%20is%20a%20lecturer%20at%20Stanford's%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmattabrahams.com%2Fbooks%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eauthor%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20says%20that%20your%20goal%20at%20parties%20or%20dinners%20is%20to%20be%20interested%2C%20not%20interesting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAbrahams%20recommends%20thinking%20about%20who%20you're%20speaking%20to%20and%20in%20what%20context%20before%20sharing.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Matt%20Abrahams%2C%20Stanford%20lecturer%2C%20communications%20consultant%2C%20author%2C%20and%20podcast%20host.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20most%20common%20mistake%20across%20all%20communication%20is%20people%20don't%20consider%20who%20they're%20talking%20to%20or%20the%20context%20in%20which%20they're%20speaking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20lecturer%20at%20Stanford's%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20where%20I%20teach%20strategic%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20end%20of%20the%20year%20and%20holiday%20time%20tend%20to%20be%20very%20stressful%20for%20people%20in%20the%20work%20setting%20and%20at%20home.%20There's%20a%20whole%20slew%20of%20traditions%20and%20things%20that%20people%20feel%20obligated%20and%20excited%20about.%20Sometimes%2C%20expectations%20might%20be%20set%20that%20are%20not%20appropriate%20or%20realistic%20at%20the%20moment%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20lead%20to%20disappointment%20or%20miscommunication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20communications%20tips%20to%20get%20through%20a%20work%20party%20or%20family%20dinner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20be%20interested%2C%20not%20interesting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20mantra%20from%20Rachel%20Greenwald%2C%20my%20colleague%20who%20is%20a%20professional%20matchmaker%20and%20dating%20coach.%20Many%20of%20us%20go%20into%20these%20work%20environments%20or%20social%20events%20and%20want%20to%20be%20amazingly%20interesting.%20We%20want%20people%20to%20find%20what%20we%20say%20really%20engaging%2C%20and%20that%20puts%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20on%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhereas%20really%20you%20want%20to%20be%20curious%2C%20you%20want%20to%20be%20interested%2C%20you%20want%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20you're%20present%20and%20paying%20attention.%20So%2C%20asking%20questions%2C%20highlighting%20things%20that%20are%20common%20in%20the%20environment%2C%20and%20getting%20others'%20opinions%20or%20their%20shared%20experience.%20Those%20skills%20are%20the%20skills%20that%20breed%20liking%20and%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20analogy%20I%20like%20to%20use%20is%20a%20hacky%20sack.%20In%20hacky%20sack%2C%20your%20whole%20goal%20is%20just%20to%20keep%20the%20ball%20up.%20Try%20phrases%20like%20%26quot%3Btell%20me%20more%26quot%3B%20or%20talk%20about%20something%20that's%20happening%20in%20the%20room%20or%20in%20the%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Wave%20the%20'white%20flag'%20before%20leaving%20a%20conversation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20auto%20racing%2C%20they%20wave%20the%20white%20flag%20before%20the%20last%20lap%20of%20the%20race.%20In%20a%20conversation%2C%20what%20I%20do%20is%20signal%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20I%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20those%20people%20over%20there%2C%20but%20before%20I%20leave%2C%20I%20have%20one%20more%20question%2C%20or%20before%20I%20leave%2C%20I'd%20love%20for%20you%20to%20tell%20me%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20about%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20signal%20you're%20going%20to%20leave%2C%20then%20you%20engage%20in%20one%20more%20conversation%20point%20or%20question.%20Then%2C%20when%20that's%20done%2C%20you%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20thank%20you.%20That%20was%20great.%20I'm%20going%20to%20talk%20to%20my%20friends.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20this%20does%20is%20it%20helps%20prepare%20everybody.%20It%20signals%20you're%20going%20one%20way%3B%20the%20other%20person's%20going%20to%20go%20the%20other.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20use%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20going%20to%20go%20to%20the%20bathroom.%26quot%3B%20And%20then%20now%20you're%20stuck%20going%20to%20the%20bathroom%20with%20the%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Consider%20who%20you're%20talking%20to%20and%20when%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20just%20want%20to%20get%20information%20out.%20We%20tend%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20we%20want%20to%20say%20rather%20than%20what%20needs%20to%20be%20said%20at%20the%20moment.%20Often%2C%20people%20don't%20consider%20who%20they're%20talking%20to%20or%20the%20context%20they're%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20advice%20is%20to%20think%20and%20reflect%20before%20speaking.%20If%20I'm%20at%20work%20and%20I'm%20pitching%20and%20proposing%20something%2C%20I%20think%20about%20what's%20the%20best%20way%20to%20frame%20it%3B%20what's%20the%20best%20time%20to%20deliver%20the%20message%3F%20But%20when%20I'm%20sitting%20around%20the%20dinner%20table%2C%20it's%20as%20if%20I%20turn%20that%20part%20of%20my%20brain%20off.%20We%20have%20to%20ask%20ourselves%20a%20couple%20of%20fundamental%20questions%20before%20we%20share%20at%20the%20party%20or%20dinner%20table%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20does%20the%20person%20know%20about%20the%20topic%20that%20I'm%20about%20to%20discuss%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20are%20the%20likely%20attitudes%20these%20people%20are%20going%20to%20have%3F%20Are%20they%20likely%20to%20be%20in%20support%20of%20what%20I'm%20saying%3F%20Are%20they%20going%20to%20be%20hesitant%20or%20resistant%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20this%20the%20appropriate%20time%20to%20bring%20this%20up%3F%20Do%20I%20have%20enough%20time%20to%20have%20this%20conversation%3F%20Is%20everybody%20tired%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Listening%20and%20reflecting%20back%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20agree%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EParaphrasing%20is%20the%20most%20important%20interpersonal%20communication%20skill.%20Having%20an%20open%20mind%2C%20being%20present%2C%20and%20being%20willing%20to%20listen%20are%20also%20important%20in%20these%20circumstances.%20Listening%20and%20reflecting%20back%20on%20what%20you%20hear%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20agree.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20times%2C%20the%20holidays%20bring%20people%20together%20that%20don't%20often%20hang%20together.%20People%20have%20different%20opinions%20and%20experiences%20in%20our%20current%20times%20and%20that%20can%20bring%20up%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20number%20one%20thing%20for%20managing%20conflict%20is%20listening%20and%20appreciating%20somebody's%20point%20of%20view%20without%20agreeing.%20And%20you%20do%20that%20through%20listening%2C%20through%20paraphrasing%20to%20confirm%20that%20you%20understand%20and%20ask%20questions%2C%20and%20then%20you%20decide%20if%20you%20want%20to%20engage%20or%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E5.%20Share%20an%20experience%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we're%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20conversation%20about%20a%20potential%20political%20issue%2C%20let's%20say%20we're%20talking%20about%20unions%20and%20unionization.%20You%20might%20have%20one%20position%2C%20and%20I%20have%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20might%20tell%20you%20about%20a%20time%20when%20I%20was%20part%20of%20a%20union%20as%20a%20teacher%2C%20and%20the%20experience%20that%20I%20had.%20Not%20to%20persuade%20you%20that%20you're%20wrong%20necessarily%2C%20but%20to%20communicate%20that%20I%20understand%20the%20issues%20on%20both%20sides%20by%20sharing%20my%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETry%20questioning%2C%20paraphrasing%2C%20and%20sharing%20a%20story%20that%20demonstrates%20your%20understanding%20of%20the%20topic.%20Before%20telling%20your%20story%2C%20ask%20what's%20the%20main%20motivation%20in%20telling%20this%20story%20and%20what's%20most%20relevant%20to%20the%20person%20you're%20talking%20to.%20If%20you%20ask%20yourself%20those%20two%20questions%2C%20your%20communication%20tends%20to%20be%20more%20focused%20and%20concise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommunication-conversation-tips-navigating-holidays-family-talking-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700648521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655d07399c7d23cb3b9e4f2a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommunication-conversation-tips-navigating-holidays-family-talking-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22These%20are%20tips%20to%20keep%20the%20holidays%20civil.%20While%20many%20strive%20to%20be%20interesting%20at%20the%20party%20or%20dinner%2C%20it's%20more%20important%20to%20be%20interested.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jgyimesi%40insider.com%20(Jenna%20Gyimesi%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommunication-conversation-tips-navigating-holidays-family-talking-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pope%20Francis%20meets%20with%20relatives%20of%20Israeli%20hostages%20and%20Palestinian%20prisoners%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700647820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105414745%2Cimgsize-620025.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.i