EI've%20seen%20people%20blow%20this%20kind%20of%20money%20on%20things%20that%20may%20be%20exciting%20but%20ultimately%20don't%20bring%20them%20lasting%20joy.%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20the%20most%20boring%20route%20possible%20with%20my%20inheritance%20so%20that%20when%20I%20do%20know%20what%20I'd%20like%20to%20spend%20it%20on%2C%20it's%20there%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20put%20my%20entire%20inheritance%20into%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-invest-in-the-sp-500%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%20index%20fund%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'll%20let%20the%20money%20sit%20there%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future%20until%20I%20have%20a%20need%20for%20it.%20When%20I%20do%2C%20I'll%20talk%20to%20my%20partner%2C%20make%20that%20decision%2C%20and%20withdraw%20the%20money%20in%20a%20way%20that%20minimizes%20my%20taxes%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20withdraw%20the%20money%2C%20I'll%20pay%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcapital-gains-tax-rates%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Elong-term%20capital-gains%20tax%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20any%20gains%20the%20sum%20has%20made%20in%20the%20stock%20market.%20It's%20quite%20straightforward%20%E2%80%94%20the%20brokerage%20firm%20will%20send%20me%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-1099%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E1099-B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%2C%20and%20I'll%20pass%20that%20along%20to%20my%20accountant.%20Taxes%20just%20mean%20I%20made%20money.%20I'll%20pay%20them%20and%20move%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you%20receive%20an%20inheritance%2C%20don't%20feel%20rushed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20inherit%20money%2C%20you%20may%20also%20be%20deep%20inside%20a%20grief%20cycle%20and%20mourning%20the%20loss%20of%20a%20person%20you%20loved.%20Because%20you%20might%20not%20be%20in%20the%20best%20mindset%20to%20make%20financial%20decisions%2C%20my%20advice%20is%20not%20to%20feel%20pressured%20or%20rush%20to%20do%20anything%20with%20the%20money%20right%20away.%20A%20great%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20give%20yourself%20at%20least%20six%20months%20before%20you%20make%20any%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you%20feel%20like%20you're%20in%20a%20more%20stable%20headspace%2C%20spend%20the%20time%20educating%20yourself%20on%20how%20to%20manage%20a%20large%20sum%20of%20money%20that%20you%20maybe%20have%20never%20had%20before%2C%20or%20hire%20a%20financial%20advisor%20or%20coach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20do%20want%20to%20give%20in%20to%20an%20urge%20to%20spend%20some%20of%20the%20money%20on%20a%20dream%20purchase%20or%20trip%2C%20put%20a%20cap%20on%20how%20much%2C%20and%20stick%20to%20that%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20thing%20you%20can%20do%20is%20keep%20your%20inheritance%20in%20a%20separate%20account%20than%20your%20day-to-day%20banking%20so%20it's%20not%20commingled%20with%20the%20money%20you%20use%20for%20bills.%20If%20it%20is%2C%20it%20might%20be%20easy%20to%20spend%20it%20fast%20and%20without%20much%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20inheritance%20doesn't%20need%20to%20lead%20to%20family%20drama%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20my%20three%20siblings%20and%20I%20split%20the%20inheritance%20from%20our%20grandmother%20equally%2C%20we%20didn't%20have%20arguments%20or%20jealousy%20that%20someone%20got%20more%20than%20the%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20can%20still%20be%20judgment%20around%20how%20other%20family%20members%20are%20spending%20their%20chunk%20of%20the%20money.%20If%20that%20happens%2C%20realize%20it's%20their%20money%20and%20they%20get%20to%20make%20their%20own%20choices.%20Try%20not%20to%20let%20it%20impact%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20kept%20a%20level%20of%20mutual%20respect%20for%20my%20siblings%20throughout%20the%20inheritance%20process%2C%20and%20it%20was%