%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Shear%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Feshear%2Fstatus%2F1726526112019382275%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edid%20post%20on%20X%20on%20Sunday%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he'd%20asked%20the%20board%20for%20their%20reasoning%20behind%20Altman's%20dismissal%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F11%2F20%2F23969586%2Fsam-altman-plotting-return-open-ai-microsoft%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Verge%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he'd%20been%20unable%20to%20obtain%20written%20documentation%20of%20their%20explanation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20planned%20to%20leave%20if%20the%20board%20didn't%20give%20him%20that%20written%20answer%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20regardless%20of%20whether%20his%20request%20was%20granted%2C%20Shear%20is%20set%20to%20depart%20the%20CEO%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20interim%20leader%2C%20he%20represented%20the%20OpenAI%20board%20in%20talks%20with%20a%20representative%20for%20Altman%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%20Bret%20Taylor%2C%20who%20was%20formerly%20co-CEO%20of%20Salesforce%2C%20served%20as%20a%20mediator%2C%20per%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShear%20indicated%20that%20those%20discussions%20led%20to%20Altman's%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20glad%20to%20have%20been%20a%20part%20of%20the%20solution%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20posted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Altman%20back%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-board-larry-summers-bret-taylor-adam-dangelo-sam-altman-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20board%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20established%2C%20OpenAI%20said%2C%20with%20Taylor%20and%20former%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Larry%20Summers%20as%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdam%20D'Angelo%2C%20who%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20original%20board%20that%20fired%20Altman%2C%20is%20staying%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20if%20Shear%20will%20remain%20at%20OpenAI%20in%20any%20capacity.%20He'd%20originally%20stepped%20down%20from%20Twitch%20in%20March%20to%20focus%20on%20his%20newborn%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%2C%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femmett-shear-openai-sam-altman-ceo-return-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700641136000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655db0939c7d23cb3b9e9254%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femmett-shear-openai-sam-altman-ceo-return-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Before%20Sam%20Altman's%20return%2C%20Emmett%20Shear%20represented%20the%20board%20in%20negotiations%20with%20the%20ousted%20OpenAI%20chief%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mloh%40businessinsider.com%20(Matthew%20Loh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A46%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femmett-shear-openai-sam-altman-ceo-return-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Billionaire%20Gautam%20Singhania's%20separation%20erases%20%24180%20mn%20at%20Raymonds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700641046000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2017-10%2F14%2Ffull%2F1507923143-1977.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbillionaire-gautam-singhania-s-separation-erases-180-mn-at-raymonds-123112200469_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20stock%20has%20tumbled%2012%20per%20cent%20since%20Nov.%2013%20when%20Singhania%20announced%20separation%20from%20Nawaz%20Singhania%2C%20his%20wife%20of%2032%20years%20and%20a%20Raymond%20board%20member%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbillionaire-gautam-singhania-s-separation-erases-180-mn-at-raymonds-123112200469_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbillionaire-gautam-singhania-s-separation-erases-180-mn-at-raymonds-123112200469_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fbillionaire-gautam-singhania-s-separation-erases-180-mn-at-raymonds-123112200469_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Any%20Form%20of%20'Tilt'%20by%20EC%20Can%20Have%20'Great%20Consequences%20for%20Democracy'%3A%20Justice%20Sanjib%20Banerjee%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F12125256%2F202111100140374935_Collegium-clears-CJ-Banerjees-transfer_SECVPF-e1636969670683.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EJustice%20Sanjib%20Banerjee%20has%20defended%20his%20April%202021%20remarks%20where%20he%20said%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felection-commission-should-be-charged-with-murder-for-allowing-rallies-madras-hc%5C%22%3Emurder%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20should%20be%20slapped%20against%20authorities%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%20for%20violating%20norms%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fex-cj-defends-rap-on-ec-if-its-seen-tilting-it-matters-in-a-democracy-9037012%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20judge%20should%20certainly%20be%20restrained.%20However%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20is%20an%20institution%20which%20has%20a%20great%20responsibility.%20So%2C%20if%20it%20is%20seen%20tilting%2C%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other%2C%20by%20even%20a%20very%20small%20degree%2C%20it%20can%20have%20great%20consequences%20for%20democracy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Banerjee%2C%20who%20recently%20retired%20as%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20Meghalaya%2C%20told%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20Madras%20high%20court%20in%20April%202021%2C%20he%20hit%20out%20sharply%20at%20the%20authorities%20of%20the%20poll%20body%20for%20violating%20COVID-19%20protocols%20during%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Assembly%20elections.%20Taking%20exception%20to%20his%20remarks%2C%20the%20poll%20body%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-moves-supreme-court-against-madras-hcs-murder-remarks%5C%22%3Emoved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20but%20the%20court%20refused%20to%20expunge%20his%20remarks.%20The%20EC%20had%20termed%20his%20remarks%20%E2%80%9Cuncalled%20for%2C%20blatantly%20disparaging%20and%20derogatory%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felection-commission-should-be-charged-with-murder-for-allowing-rallies-madras-hc%5C%22%3EElection%20Commission%20Should%20Be%20Charged%20With%20Murder%20for%20Allowing%20Rallies%3A%20Madras%20HC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%2010-month%20stint%20at%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%2C%20Justice%20Banjeree%20had%20been%20in%20the%20news%20quite%20a%20few%20times%2C%20ruffling%20the%20feathers%20of%20many.%20His%20transfer%20to%20Meghalaya%20high%20court%20in%20November%202021%20was%20described%20by%20many%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpunishment%20posting%E2%80%9D%2C%20for%20such%20a%20transfer%20from%20a%20relatively%20bigger%20higher%20court%20to%20a%20smaller%20one%20was%20seen%20as%20unusual.%20After%20about%20two%20years%2C%20he%20retired%20as%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20Meghalaya%20high%20court%20on%20November%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20at%20his%20remarks%20that%20supposedly%20led%20to%20his%20transfer%20in%20November%202021%2C%20Justice%20Banerjee%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20case%20was%20being%20heard%20(in%20Madras%20HC)%20for%20a%20while%20and%20I%20felt%20there%20were%20some%20aberrations%20which%20is%20why%20those%20observations%20were%20made.%20Crowding%20in%20rallies%20and%20not%20following%20Covid%20protocol%20was%20certainly%20a%20concern%20and%20when%20the%20elections%20in%20West%20Bengal%20were%20held%20in%20eight%20phases%2C%20why%20was%20it%20held%20in%20a%20single%20phase%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%3F%20You%20have%20to%20look%20at%20it%20in%20that%20context%20and%20not%20pick%20just%20two%20sentences.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20went%20on%20to%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20one%20cannot%20say%20that%20the%20court%20can%E2%80%99t%20make%20any%20observations.%20Lawyers%20cannot%20be%20expected%20to%20argue%20with%20a%20wall.%20They%20have%20to%20get%20indications%20from%20the%20bench%20so%20they%20can%20tailor%20their%20case%20accordingly.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Banerjee%20said%20he%20is%20not%20concerned%20about%20what%20led%20to%20his%20transfer%20to%20Meghalaya%20high%20court.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20sure%20there%20were%20cogent%20reasons%20for%20my%20transfer%20but%20I%20am%20not%20aware%20of%20it.%20I%20received%20an%20email%20(from%20then%20CJI%20N.V.%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20office)%20and%20I%20said%20yes.%20Once%20you%20become%20a%20judge%2C%20you%20cannot%20have%20any%20ambitions%20of%20holding%20a%20particular%20office.%20So%20there%20was%20no%20question%20of%20me%20not%20consenting%20to%20the%20transfer.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20transfer%20was%20notified%20on%20November%209%2C%202021%2C%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Collegium%2C%20which%20said%20that%20a%20decision%20to%20that%20effect%20was%20taken%20on%20September%2016%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20no%20reason%20cited%20for%20his%20transfer%20by%20the%20Collegium%2C%20Justice%20said%20that%20the%20email%20he%20received%20from%20the%20CJI%20office%20only%20indicated%20that%20his%20transfer%20would%20be%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinterest%20of%20better%20administration%20of%20justice%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Banerjee%20says%20he%20is%20least%20concerned%20about%20the%20reasons%20that%20led%20to%20his%20transfer.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20would%20not%20have%20had%20it%20any%20other%20way.%20The%20work%20that%20happened%20in%20Meghalaya%20during%20my%20stint%20was%20very%20important.%20In%20my%2011%20months%20in%20Madras%2C%20I%20had%20very%20rewarding%20judicial%20work.%20But%20in%20Meghalaya%2C%20there%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20lot%20of%20judicial%20work%20but%20we%20focused%20on%20infrastructure%20building.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20his%20stint%20at%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%2C%20he%20says%20that%20he%20never%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20status%20quoist.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20idea%20is%20that%20a%20Chief%20Justice%20who%20comes%20from%20outside%20takes%20a%20dispassionate%20view%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20appointments%20or%20other%20aspects%2C%20there%20is%20a%20flip%20side%20that%20they%20could%20end%20up%20being%20status%20quo-ists%20without%20wanting%20to%20ruffle%20too%20many%20feathers.%20By%20and%20large%2C%20the%20office%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20is%20considered%20a%20stepping%20stone%20for%20Supreme%20Court%20judgeship.%20It%20is%20to%20be%20somewhere%20but%20look%20elsewhere%20and%20not%20take%20steps%20to%20actively%20address%20the%20uncle-judge%20syndrome%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20appointments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Banerjee%2C%20who%20had%20been%20in%20the%20system%20for%20two%20decades%2C%20says%20that%20corruption%20in%20the%20higher%20judiciary%20worries%20him.%20%E2%80%9CPunitive%20transfers%20are%20not%20enough.%20Corruption%20is%20an%20unimpeachable%20offence%20but%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20gather%20evidence.%20These%20activities%20are%20not%20done%20in%20broad%20daylight%20but%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20collect%20some%20evidence%20of%20corruption.%20However%2C%20impeachment%20is%20a%20political%20solution.%20A%20compromised%20judge%20is%20convenient%20for%20all%20political%20parties.%20This%20is%20an%20aspect%20which%20erodes%20faith%20in%20the%20system%20and%20needs%20to%20be%20tackled.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Banerjee%20enrolled%20as%20an%20advocate%20in%20November%201990%20and%20began%20practicing%20principally%20in%20the%20Calcutta%20high%20court%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20He%20was%20elevated%20to%20the%20Bench%20as%20a%20judge%20in%20June%202006%20and%20took%20over%20as%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%20on%20January%204%2C%202021%2C%20before%20he%20was%20transferred%20to%20Meghalaya%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700640936000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F12125256%2F202111100140374935_Collegium-clears-CJ-Banerjees-transfer_SECVPF-e1636969670683.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fany-form-of-tilt-by-ec-can-have-great-consequences-for-democracy-justice-sanjib-banerjee%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justice%20Banerjee%2C%20who%20recently%20retired%20as%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20Meghalaya%20high%20court%2C%20defended%20his%20April%202021%20remarks%20when%20he%20said%20the%20authorities%20of%20Election%20Commission%20should%20be%20charged%20with%20murder%20for%20violating%20COVID-19%20protocols.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fany-form-of-tilt-by-ec-can-have-great-consequences-for-democracy-justice-sanjib-banerjee%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22There%20are%20now%20more%20central%20banks%20cutting%20interest%20rates%20than%20those%20hiking%20them%3A%20Deutsche%20Bank%20analysis%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F644feaa4da6d7b0019bdcc4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221392%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell.%3Cp%3ELiu%20Jie%2F