-news%2Fsam-altman-to-return-as-ceo-of-openai-new-interim-board-announced-123112200315_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fworld-news%2Fsam-altman-to-return-as-ceo-of-openai-new-interim-board-announced-123112200315_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Oblique%20Power%3A%20How%20the%20Wealthiest%20Few%20Set%20the%20Research%20Agenda%20of%20Political%20Science%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22115058%2Fpexels-brett-sayles-1069000.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20almost%20banal%20to%20say%20that%20%E2%80%9Cknowledge%20is%20power%E2%80%9D%20and%20yet%2C%20even%20then%2C%20miss%20the%20woods%20for%20the%20trees.%20Most%20of%20us%20tend%20to%20think%20at%20a%20personal%20level%20or%20to%20see%20individuals%20with%20%E2%80%98knowledge%E2%80%99%20using%20it%20to%20get%20what%20they%20want.%20But%20when%20we%20come%20to%20think%20about%20the%20small%20number%20of%20institutions%20that%20more%20or%20less%20monopolise%20the%20production%20of%20knowledge%20%E2%80%93%20corporations%2C%20foundations%2C%20universities%2C%20state%20agencies%2C%20corporate%20media%20%E2%80%93%20the%20individualist%20approach%20becomes%20obsolete.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EBig%20knowledge%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20produced%20by%20relatively%20few%20people%20linked%20with%20or%20rather%20employed%20by%20and%20embedded%20within%20very%20rich%20and%20powerful%20institutions%20wedded%20to%20the%20status%20quo%20or%20to%20the%20management%20of%20change%20such%20that%20any%20change%20is%20moderate%2C%20minimal%2C%20functional%20for%20elites%2C%20and%20fails%20to%20alter%20the%20patterns%20of%20fundamental%20power%20distributions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20probably%20no%20society%20quite%20like%20the%20US%20in%20this%20regard.%20It%20is%20a%20knowledge%20superpower.%20Books%2C%20magazines%2C%20universities%2C%20academic%20journals%2C%20scientific%20patents%2C%20intellectual%20property%2C%20Nobel%20prizes%2C%20Hollywood%E2%80%99s%20cultural%20output%2C%20the%20global%20reach%20of%20US%20news%20and%20other%20media%20%E2%80%93%20no%20other%20society%20comes%20close%20to%20matching%20America%E2%80%99s%20knowledge%20production%20and%20dissemination%20machine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPolitical%20science%20as%20a%20university%20discipline%20is%20said%20to%20have%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20its%20mission%20to%20unravel%20the%20mysteries%20of%20power%2C%20who%20holds%20it%2C%20who%20benefits%2C%20and%20how%20it%20works.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20advertising%20in%20attractive%20brochures%20and%20glitzy%20websites.%20The%20plain%20truth%20is%20a%20world%20apart.%20Indeed%2C%20one%20could%20argue%20that%20the%20purpose%20of%20political%20science%20in%20the%20US%20is%20to%20obscure%20the%20loci%20and%20operations%20of%20power%2C%20a%20magic%20trick%20of%20smoke%20and%20mirrors%20that%20casts%20a%20veil%20over%20what%20we%2C%20the%20people%2C%20instinctively%20know%20is%20a%20con%20though%20few%20have%20the%20tools%20to%20surgically%20wield%20a%20scalpel%20to%20pierce%20that%20veil.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20there%20are%20enough%20political%20scientists%20who%20have%20such%20tools%20and%20are%20increasingly%20using%20them%20to%20devastating%20effect.%20Ido%20Orren%E2%80%99s%20work%20stands%20out%2C%20as%20does%20Robert%20Vitalis%E2%80%99s.%20Orren%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cornellpress.cornell.edu%2Fbook%2F9780801478949%2Four-enemies-and-us%2F%23bookTabs%3D1%5C%22%3Eshowed%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20US%20political%20science%20serves%20US%20foreign%20policy%20interests%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20portrayal%20of%20Nazi%20Germany%20and%20Fascist%20Italy%20in%20the%20pages%20of%20its%20flagship%20journal%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmerican%20Political%20Science%20Review%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20those%20states%20were%20seen%20as%20exemplars%20of%20efficient%20administration%20and%20modernisation.%20In%20the%201940s%2C%20of%20course%20and%20into%20the%20post-1945%20period%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EAPSR%3C%2Fem%3E%20discovered%20the%20dangers%20of%20unrestricted%20state%20power.%20Vitalis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cornellpress.cornell.edu%2Fbook%2F9780801456695%2Fwhite-world-order-black-power-politics%2F%5C%22%3Eshows%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20racist%20and%20colonial%20attitudes%20saturated%20the%20field%20of%20international%20relations%20(IR)%2C%20and%20led%20to%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20elitist%20Council%20on%20Foreign%20Relations%20think%20tank.%20Its%20house%20organ%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EForeign%20Affairs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20was%20originally%20called%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EJournal%20of%20Race%20Development%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20IR%20as%20a%20field%20had%20as%20its%20focal%20point%20the%20study%20and%20management%20of%20race%20relations%20on%20a%20worldwide%20basis%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20That%20is%2C%20the%20maintenance%20of%20white%20supremacy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20330px)%2085vw%2C%20330px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22114308%2F71yUb5Ws2KL._SL1500_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22330%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22114308%2F71yUb5Ws2KL._SL1500_.jpg%20797w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22114308%2F71yUb5Ws2KL._SL1500_-199x300.jpg%20199w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22114308%2F71yUb5Ws2KL._SL1500_-680x1024.jpg%20680w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685820%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22497%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EEmily%20Hauptmann%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EFoundations%20and%20American%20Political%20Science%3A%20The%20Transformation%20of%20a%20Discipline%2C%201945-1970%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EUniversity%20Press%20of%20Kansas%20(November%202022)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFoundations%20and%20American%20Political%20Science%3A%20The%20Transformation%20of%20a%20Discipline%2C%201945-1970%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3EEmily%20Hauptmann%E2%80%99s%20excellent%20study%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20welcome%20and%20timely.%20It%20adds%20to%20a%20growing%20literature%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20the%20political%20power%20of%20elites%2C%20especially%20philanthropic%20foundations%2C%20and%20brings%20in%20universities%20as%20institutions%20with%20their%20own%20interests%20in%20winning%20research%20funding%20from%20a%20growing%20federal%20budget%20dedicated%20to%20servicing%20a%20military-industrial%20complex%20driven%20by%20Cold%20War%20competition.%20It%20is%20well-researched%20in%20primary%20materials%2C%20well-organised%2C%20and%20accessibly%20written.%20It%20should%20be%20read%20by%20all%20social%20science%20scholars%2C%20historians%20of%20ideas%20and%20political%20science%2C%20historians%20of%20the%20development%20of%20the%20American%20university%2C%20and%20the%20influence%20of%20the%20Ford%2C%20Carnegie%20and%20Rockefeller%20foundations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20study%20of%20power%20is%20at%20the%20core%20of%20political%20science%20%C2%A0%E2%80%93%20but%20who%20decides%20how%20to%20get%20to%20the%20core%20of%20where%20power%20lies%20in%20any%20society%2C%20how%20it%20works%2C%20and%20who%20matters%20in%20politics%20and%20political%20change%2C%20is%20itself%20a%20key%20power.%20Who%20defines%20political%20science%E2%80%99s%20core%20elements%20therefore%20sets%20research%20agendas%2C%20directs%20funding%2C%20builds%20institutes%20and%20departments%2C%20dominates%20professional%20societies%2C%20major%20disciplinary%20journals%E2%80%99%20orientations%20and%20priorities%20and%20peer%20reviewers%2C%20who%20gets%20promoted%20and%20celebrated%20%E2%80%93%20and%2C%20equally%2C%20who%20does%20not.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20American%20political%20science%2C%20the%20power%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20few%20preoccupies%20a%20tiny%20number%20and%20proportion%20of%20its%20political%20scientists%E2%80%99%20research%20agendas%2C%20course%20themes%2C%20and%20reading%20lists.%20The%20rich%20and%20powerful%20do%20not%20like%20and%20do%20not%20fund%20independent%20studies%20of%20their%20class%2C%20activities%20or%20networks.%20That%20in%20itself%20is%20power%20to%20operate%20relatively%20free%20of%20scrutiny.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20another%20form%20of%20%E2%80%9Coblique%20power%E2%80%9D%20as%20Emily%20Hauptmann%20describes%20it%20%E2%80%93%20it%20directs%20attention%20to%20the%20problems%20of%20society%20and%20politics%20usually%20rooted%20in%20alleged%20irrational%20mass%20behaviour%2C%20the%20illusions%20and%20frailties%20of%20the%20electorate%2C%20the%20power%20in%20the%20land%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20educated%20and%20informed%20away%20from%20a%20%E2%80%98mob%20mentality%E2%80%99%20and%20towards%20reason%20and%20realism.%20American%20political%20science%20is%2C%20or%20thinks%20it%20is%2C%20that%20self-proclaimed%20%E2%80%9Csecular%20priesthood%E2%80%9D%20that%20Walter%20Lippman%20wanted%20to%20see%20to%20handle%20the%20dangerous%20masses%2C%20manage%20the%20%E2%80%9Ctyranny%20of%20the%20majority%E2%80%9D%20and%20engineer%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconsent%20of%20the%20governed%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAmerican%20foundations%20exercise%20%E2%80%98oblique%E2%80%99%20power%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20obliquely%20powerful%20philanthropic%20foundations%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20Hauptmann%E2%80%99s%20incisive%20study%20even%20define%20themselves%20out%20of%20the%20core%20of%20power%20in%20the%20US%20and%20therefore%20of%20the%20attention%20of%20political%20science.%20The%20powerful%20define%20themselves%20as%20beyond%20politics%2C%20ideology%2C%20business%2C%20the%20state%20%E2%80%93%20as%20somewhere%20else%20entirely%20neutral%2C%20objective%2C%20even%20scientific%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9Cthird%20sector%E2%80%9D.%20Above%20and%20beyond%20too%20much%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHauptmann%E2%80%99s%20study%20deconstructs%20and%20effectively%20and%20carefully%20annihilates%20this%20self-image%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98big%203%E2%80%99%20foundations%20%E2%80%93%20Ford%2C%20Rockefeller%20and%20Carnegie%20%E2%80%93%20their%20remaking%20of%20the%20vision%20for%20the%20technocratic%20possibilities%20of%20social%20sciences%20and%20the%20uses%20of%20political%20science.%20Her%20focus%20in%20this%20essential%20and%20landmark%20study%20is%20those%20three%20big%20foundations%20and%20two%20public%20research%20universities%20%E2%80%93%20Michigan%2C%20and%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%20%E2%80%93%20between%201945-70.%20The%20period%20was%20transformative%20the%20world%20over%2C%20including%20for%20the%20bright%20shining%20light%20that%20American%20power%20promised%20the%20world%20after%20the%20defeat%20of%20fascism%2C%20and%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20deadly%20ideological%20and%20military%20struggles%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20otherwise%20better%20known%20by%20historians%20as%20US%20expansionism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmily%20Hauptmann%20has%20spent%20years%20studying%20the%20original%20records%20of%20each%20of%20the%20three%20foundations%2C%20numerous%20personal%20paper%20collections%2C%20official%20university%20records%2C%20and%20oral%20histories.%20Those%20papers%20have%20been%20researched%20in%20depth%2C%20compared%20with%20one%20another%20and%20synthesised%20and%20cross-referenced.%20The%20resulting%20book%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20definitive%20word%20on%20the%20history%20and%20development%20of%20US%20political%20science%2C%20and%20the%20forces%20that%20conceived%20of%20the%20discipline%E2%80%99s%20principal%20preoccupations%20and%20methodologies%2C%20funded%20it%2C%20shaped%20its%20contours%2C%20kept%20it%20connected%20with%20what%20President%20Dwight%20Eisenhower%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98military-industrial-complex%E2%80%99.%20This%20was%20a%20discipline%20re-made%20for%20war%20and%20Cold%20War%2C%20the%20gathering%20of%20intelligence%20on%20the%20US%20electorate%2C%20and%20developing%20knowledge%20for%20use%20in%20the%20titanic%20struggle%20between%20capitalism%20and%20communism.%20It%20was%2C%20therefore%2C%20part%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98whole-of-society%E2%80%99%20elite%20mobilisation%20behind%20US%20expansionism%2C%20against%20the%20domestic%20and%20global%20Left%2C%20but%20particularly%20nationalist%20anti-colonial%20struggles%20in%20what%20became%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%98Third%20World%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHauptmann%20places%20her%20work%20in%20that%20context%20%E2%80%93%20World%20War%20II%20service%20by%20leading%20foundation%20and%20academic%20figures%20and%20institutions%2C%20that%20bled%20liberally%20into%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20connected%20symbiotically%20to%20the%20broader%20US%20political%20economy%2C%20the%20power%20of%20a%20growing%20military-industrial%20complex%20and%20its%20core%20in%20the%20federal%20government.%20The%20book%20explores%20networks%20of%20power%20that%20span%20the%20state%20and%20private%20sectors%20that%20implicate%20both%20rather%20than%20exonerate%20them%20for%20the%20real%20world%20of%20US%20power%20%E2%80%93%20as%20dominated%20not%20only%20by%20great%20corporate%20wealth%2C%20an%20increasingly%20powerful%20federal%20government%20executive%20and%20its%20plethora%20of%20national%20security%20agencies%2C%20and%20a%20growing%20powerful%20military%20and%20even%20more%20what%20C.%20Wright%20Mills%20called%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmilitary%20definition%20of%20reality%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20nuclear%20age.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPolitical%20science%2C%20area%20studies%2C%20and%20IR%20form%20a%20nexus%20here%20that%20served%20to%20place%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20US%20knowledge-power%20disciplines%20that%20focused%20on%20and%20were%20rooted%20in%20both%20the%20imaginary%20of%20American%20exceptionalism%20at%20home%2C%20to%20furnish%20a%20mission%20of%20improvement%20and%20reform%2C%20and%20a%20war%20machine%20with%20personnel%20from%20the%20best%20universities%2C%20the%20advanced%20guard%20of%20freedom.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBook%20details%20resistance%20to%20elites%20too%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmily%20Hauptmann%20has%20performed%20a%20great%20service%20to%20social%20and%20political%20science%20and%20understanding%20%E2%80%93%20explaining%20by%20showing%20via%20primary%20evidence%20how%20power%20really%20works%20in%20liberal%20democratic%20America.%20By%20so%20doing%20she%20has%20also%20exposed%20liberal%20democracy%E2%80%99s%20shortcomings%2C%20failings%2C%20exclusions%2C%20and%20marginalisations%20%E2%80%93%20a%20necessary%20by-product%20of%20what%20and%20whom%20that%20society%20prioritises.%20In%20its%20starkest%20result%2C%20implicitly%20on%20the%20whole%2C%20Hauptmann%20shows%20how%20unstable%20the%20whole%20structure%20really%20is%20%E2%80%93%20because%20the%20excluded%20and%20marginal%20are%20never%20silent%2C%20never%20consistently%20weak%20%E2%80%93%20the%20%E2%80%9Ciron%20law%20of%20oligarchy%E2%80%9D%20of%20Robert%20Michels%20has%20its%20counterpart%2C%20as%20Alvin%20Gouldner%20said%2C%20in%20an%20%E2%80%9Ciron%20law%20of%20democracy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20documents%20the%20faculty%20and%20student%20resistances%20that%20broke%20out%20in%20the%201960s%20over%20an%20array%20of%20issues%20including%20opposition%20to%20the%20Vietnam%20War%2C%20rejection%20of%20the%20role%20of%20many%20political%20scientist%20consultants%20in%20the%20State%20Department%20and%20other%20agencies%2C%20the%20out-of-touch%20character%20of%20the%20curriculum.%20As%20Professor%20Sheldon%20Wolin%20argued%2C%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20faculty%20and%20students%20wanted%20a%20university%20that%20enriched%20human%20life%2C%20and%20to%20%E2%80%9Cend%20our%20University%E2%80%99s%20complicity%20with%E2%80%A6%20%5Bthe%20Vietnam%5D%20war.%E2%80%9D%20Student%20strikers%20also%20argued%20that%20universities%20ought%20not%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctrain%20students%20to%E2%80%A6%20support%2C%20justify%2C%20and%20implement%20the%20American%20world%20system%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20Mainstream%20political%20science%20faculty%2C%20however%2C%20rejected%20such%20calls%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpoliticising%E2%80%9D%20political%20science%20while%20acknowledging%20the%20role%20so%20many%20of%20their%20number%20played%20in%20war-oriented%20agencies%20of%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Hauptmann%20shows%2C%20those%20in%20power%20define%20what%20is%20politics%20and%20what%20is%20not.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22115327%2FUnited_States_Department_of_State_headquarters.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22115327%2FUnited_States_Department_of_State_headquarters.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22115327%2FUnited_States_Department_of_State_headquarters-300x239.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22115327%2FUnited_States_Department_of_State_headquarters-410x325.jpg%20410w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685823%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22815%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHeadquarters%20of%20the%20US%20State%20Department.%20Photo%3A%20AgnosticPreachersKid%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%203.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBuilding%20and%20defending%20the%20canon%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20Emily%20Hauptmann%E2%80%99s%20study%20shows%20is%20in%20effect%20how%20the%20major%20and%20oldest%20US%20foundations%2C%20the%20US%20federal%20government%2Fstate%2C%20and%20the%20postwar%20research%20universities%20built%20the%20canon%20in%20political%20science%2C%20area%20studies%20and%20IR%20etc%20%E2%80%93%20the%20core%20studies%20in%20graduate%20and%20PhD%20programmes%20that%20defined%20what%20the%20social%20sciences%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20%E2%80%93%20questions%2C%20issues%2C%20theories%2C%20methods%2C%20cases%20%E2%80%93%20and%20what%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20%E2%80%93%20especially%2C%20and%20starkly%2C%20marginalising%20the%20likes%20of%20Wright%20Mills%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobal.oup.com%2Facademic%2Fproduct%2Fthe-power-elite-9780195133547%3Fcc%3Dus%26lang%3Den%26%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Power%20Elite%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(1956)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20It%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20possible%20to%20write%20a%20deeply%20researched%20critical%20book%2C%20based%20on%20years%20of%20study%20and%20toil%2C%20and%20have%20it%20either%20largely%20ignored%20or%20criticised%20for%20failing%20to%20conform%20to%20the%20dominant%20methodology.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20wrong%20kind%20of%20knowledge!%20Thinking%20the%20unthinkable.%20The%20free%20market%20of%20ideas%2C%20denied.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20core%20argument%20of%20Hauptmann%E2%80%99s%20study%20is%20that%20the%20so-called%20behavioural%20revolution%20in%20American%20political%20science%20represented%20a%20move%20by%20several%20key%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20foundations%2C%20universities%2C%20and%20political%20scientists%2C%20each%20for%20their%20specific%20reasons%20and%20interests%20%E2%80%93%20was%20neither%20inevitable%20nor%20necessarily%20beneficial%20in%20studying%20and%20understanding%20how%20power%20actually%20works%20in%20the%20real%20world%20of%20US%20politics.%20It%20was%20a%20concerted%20intervention%20to%20produce%20specific%20kinds%20of%20political%20scientific%20legitimate%20knowledge%2C%20with%20its%20academic%20apparatus%20of%20journal%20articles%2C%20canonical%20texts%2C%20field%20leaders%2C%20departments%2C%20doctoral%20programmes%2C%20and%20research%20linked%20with%20political%20institutions%2C%20especially%20the%20main%20political%20parties%2C%20the%20expanding%20federal%20government%2C%20and%20the%20military-industrial%20complex.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBehaviouralism%20seeks%20to%20uncover%20and%20address%20the%20behaviours%20of%20individuals%20and%20groups%20%E2%80%93%20voting%20behaviour%20for%20example%20%E2%80%93%20in%20order%20to%20generate%20statistical%20knowledge%20for%20use%20by%20the%20powers%20that%20be.%20Its%20main%20focus%20then%20is%20on%20the%20electorate%20and%20range%20of%20interest%20groups%20in%20a%20competitive%20system%20where%20no%20class%20or%20race%20monopolises%20power.%20Behaviouralism%20is%20fundamentally%20predicated%20on%20a%20pluralistic%2C%20mid-20th%20century%20version%20of%20US%20democracy%2C%20a%20society%20of%20groups%20engaged%20in%20perfect%20competition%20with%20one%20another.%20It%20is%20also%20fundamentally%20positivistic%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%20%E2%80%98scientific%E2%80%99%20and%20value-free%20%E2%80%93%20because%2C%20it%20is%20claimed%2C%20it%20is%20based%20on%20objective%2C%20quantifiable%20approaches%20to%20explain%20and%20predict%20political%20behaviour.%20Structures%20of%20racial%2C%20colonial%2C%20elite%20and%20class%20power%2C%20gendered%20patriarchal%20power%20relations%20and%20institutions%2C%20the%20sinews%20of%20social%2C%20economic%20and%20political%20life%2C%20qualitative%20studies%20of%20documents%2C%20texts%2C%20of%20the%20rich%20textures%20of%20human%20life%2C%20are%20beyond%20the%20canon.%20They%20are%20not%20%E2%80%98real%E2%80%99%20political%20science%2C%20according%20to%20this%20view.%20Of%20course%2C%20there%20are%20nuances%20involved%2C%20but%20most%20behaviouralists%20would%20accept%20some%20or%20all%20of%20the%20above%20as%20essential%20to%20the%20postwar%20revolution%20in%20American%20political%20science.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20beneficiaries%20of%20fellowships%20and%20grants%20from%20behavioural%20studies%20programmes%20of%20funding%20such%20as%20Robert%20Dahl%20openly%20challenged%20Mills%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20elite%20thesis%20and%20Floyd%20Hunter%E2%80%99s%20community%20power%20structures%20research%20from%20an%20overtly%20methodological%20approach%20%E2%80%93%20why%20did%20they%20not%20conduct%20behavioural%20decisionmaking%20case%20studies%20%E2%80%93%20rather%20than%20the%20foundational%20premises%20of%20their%20analyses%20of%20power.%20Those%20challenged%20the%20pluralistic%20framing%20in%20fundamental%20ways.%20Dahl%20et%20al%20therefore%20in%20their%20reactions%20showed%20that%20the%20knowledge%20networks%20around%20behavioural%20political%20science%20both%20build%20a%20specific%20kind%20of%20discipline%20as%20well%20as%20defending%20its%20turf%20against%20resistance%20and%20alternatives.%20In%20this%2C%20their%20connection%20with%20and%20benefits%20from%20what%20Hauptmann%20refers%20to%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9Cuniversity%20knowledge%20economy%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpostwar%20federal%20research%20economy%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Corganised%20war%20research%20economy%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20provide%20a%20material%20explanation.%20This%20is%20no%20ivory%20tower%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20academic%20combat%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20canon.%20Knowledge%20and%20power%2C%20and%20power%20and%20knowledge%2C%20Siamese%20twins%20joined%20at%20the%20hip%2C%20heart%20and%20head.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHarold%20Laski%20was%20surely%20right%20%E2%80%93%20it%20takes%20a%20mere%20announcement%20by%20a%20rich%20foundation%20of%20a%20funded%20research%20programme%20for%20numerous%20scholars%20to%20declare%20that%20they%20had%20always%20been%20interested%20in%20the%20matter!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20G.%20William%20Domhoff%2C%20notes%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20agenda%20underlying%20Dahl%E2%80%99s%201957%20article%20on%20the%20concept%20of%20power%2C%20which%20consists%20of%20Max%20Weber%20souped%20up%20with%20probability%20equations%20that%20never%20proved%20useful%2C%20became%20even%20more%20obvious%20in%20his%20follow-up%20paper%20on%20power%2C%20%E2%80%98A%20Critique%20of%20the%20Ruling%20Elite%20Model%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20which%20he%20summarily%20dismissed%20both%20Hunter%20and%20Mills%20with%20the%20resounding%20conclusion%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20remarkable%20and%20indeed%20astounding%20fact%20that%20neither%20Professor%20Mills%20nor%20Professor%20Hunter%20has%20seriously%20attempted%20to%20examine%20an%20array%20of%20specific%20cases%20to%20test%20his%20major%20hypothesis%E2%80%9D.%20Dahl%20thereby%20took%20the%20substantive%20issues%20off%20the%20table%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwhorulesamerica.ucsc.edu%2Ftheory%2Fmills_critique.html%5C%22%3Eturned%20the%20argument%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20seemingly%20methodological%20one%2C%20although%20it%20was%20actually%20an%20argument%20about%20philosophies%20of%20science%20that%20he%20was%20invoking%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EAcademia%20is%20no%20ivory%20tower%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHauptmann%20makes%20very%20clear%20that%20her%20work%20stands%20more%20in%20the%20tradition%20of%20Ido%20Orren%2C%20Nicholas%20Guilhot%2C%20and%20Robert%20Vitalis%20%E2%80%93%20to%20show%20how%20external%20factors%2C%20and%20not%20internal%20ones%20alone%20%E2%80%93%20have%20powerfully%20shaped%20the%20political%20science%20and%20IR%20disciplines%20that%20are%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20legitimising%20US%20power%20%E2%80%93%20in%20its%20geopolitical%20rivalries%2C%20its%20ideological%20wars%2C%20its%20construction%20and%20defence%20of%20racialised-class%20hierarchies%2C%20and%20defences%20of%20colonialism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20focusing%20in%20depth%20on%20two%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20public%20universities%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20whose%20political%20science%20departments%20rank%20among%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20strongest%2C%20Michigan%20and%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley%2C%20Hauptmann%E2%80%99s%20analysis%20and%20conclusions%20may%20be%20considered%20generalisable%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20American%20system%20of%20higher%20education.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndeed%2C%20the%20power%20of%20money%2C%20and%20business%20interests%2C%20in%20American%20universities%20is%20hardly%20unknown.%20Thorsten%20Veblen%20pointed%20this%20out%20in%20great%20detail%20in%20his%20book%20of%201916%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Higher%20Learning%20in%20America%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20subtitle%20of%20which%20was%20something%20like%20%E2%80%9Ca%20memorandum%20on%20the%20conduct%20of%20the%20universities%20by%20businessmen%E2%80%9D.%20But%20because%20this%20is%20precisely%20the%20sort%20of%20knowledge%20that%20dare%20not%20speak%20its%20name%2C%20the%20message%20that%20gets%20perpetually%20buried%20needs%20repetition%2C%20new%20studies%2C%20constant%20reminders%20of%20how%20and%20for%20whom%20universities%20actually%20work.%20As%20well%20as%20where%20the%20resistances%20emerge%20from%20and%20influence%20developments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEmily%20Hauptmann%20has%20done%20this%20with%20great%20skill%20and%20scholarship%2C%20through%20a%20book%20that%20is%20a%20must-read%2C%20take-note%2C%20and%20act-upon-and-develop%20with%20more%20research.%20And%20drive%20the%20message%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20always%20impressive%20to%20me%20how%20much%20collective%20effort%20%E2%80%9Cindividual%E2%80%9D%20freedom%20takes%20to%20produce%20it%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20ways%20shown%20in%20this%20remarkable%20and%20enduring%20work%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20system%20of%20individual%20freedom%20and%20free%20enterprise%20is%20in%20fact%20a%20vastly%20orchestrated%20web%20of%20networks%20and%20flows%20of%20copious%20amounts%20of%20taxpayers%E2%80%99%20money%20over%20decades%20and%20decades%3B%20corporate-welfare%20money%20that%20is%20tax-exempt%20under%20cover%20of%20its%20non-political%20deployments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20a%20vast%2C%20complex%20and%20dense%20system%20of%20knowledge%20for%20combat%20that%20builds%20%E2%80%9Cempires%20of%20the%20mind%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20material%20foundations%20of%20a%20state-corporate%20system%20of%20political%20economy%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20a%20liberal%20international%20system%20whose%20very%20foundations%20appear%20to%20be%20cracked%20and%20even%20crumbling%2C%20which%20finds%20itself%20today%20in%20its%20very%20heartlands%20being%20written%20about%20by%20CIA-linked%20students%20of%20civil%20wars%20as%20edging%20closer%20and%20closer%20to%20a%20repeat%20of%201861-1865.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fiparmar%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EInderjeet%20Parmar%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20professor%20of%20international%20politics%20and%20associate%20dean%20of%20research%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Policy%20and%20Global%20Affairs%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20a%20fellow%20of%20the%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20and%20a%20columnist%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20He%20is%20an%20International%20Fellow%20at%20the%20ROADS%20Initiative%20think%20tank%2C%20Islamabad%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20author%20of%20several%20books%20including%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3EFoundations%20of%20the%20American%20Century%3Ci%3E.%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20history%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20powers%20of%20the%20US%20Foreign%20Policy%20Establishment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700634269000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F22115058%2Fpexels-brett-sayles-1069000.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Foblique-power-political-science-research-agenda-emily-hauptmann-book%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Emily%20Hauptmann's%20book%20'Foundations%20and%20American%20Political%20Science'%20shows%20how%20US%20universities%2C%20foundations%20and%20the%20state%20mobilise%20knowledge%20for%20power%20to%20obscure%20where%20it%20lies%20and%20how%20it%20works.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Foblique-power-political-science-research-agenda-emily-hauptmann-book%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22OpenAI%20Reaches%20Deal%20With%20Sam%20Altman%20to%20Return%20as%20CEO%2C%20With%20New%20Board%20in%20Place%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700633914000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FSam-Altman-OpenAI.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235805171%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20week%20ago%2C%20OpenAI%E2%80%99s%20board%20fired%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman.%20Now%2C%20the%20pioneering%20artificial%20intelligence%20startup%2C%20which%20created%20buzzy%20AI%20chatbot%20ChatGPT%2C%20is%20bringing%20him%20back.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20reached%20an%20agreement%20in%20principle%20for%20Sam%20Altman%20to%20return%20to%20OpenAI%20as%20CEO%20with%20a%20new%20initial%20board%20of%20Bret%20Taylor%20(Chair)%2C%20Larry%20Summers%2C%20and%20Adam%20D%E2%80%99Angelo%2C%E2%80%9D%2