2C%20they%20opened%20their%20Shelter%20Space%20for%20LGBTQI%2B%20youth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20thing%20we%20know%20as%20queer%20people%20is%20that%20our%20homes%20are%20not%20always%20the%20safest%20spaces.%20Many%20queer%20people%20get%20kicked%20out%20of%20their%20homes%20out%20of%20ignorance%20and%20fear%20of%20what%20the%20larger%20society%20may%20think%20if%20their%20child%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20follow%20conventional%20rules%20of%20gender.%20Many%20queer%20people%20endure%20homelessness.%20In%20addition%20to%20all%20this%2C%20when%20there%20is%20a%20crisis%20like%20COVID-19%20or%20the%20current%20armed%20conflict%20in%20Manipur%2C%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20place%20to%20stay%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Sadam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shelter%20space%20is%20a%20crowdfunded%20initiative%2C%20informs%20Sadam%2C%20where%20queer%20people%2C%20who%20are%20rendered%20homeless%2C%20can%20stay%20for%2010%20days%20free%20of%20charge.%20After%2010%20days%2C%20if%20people%20can%20afford%20it%2C%20they%20are%20asked%20to%20pay%20Rs%20100%20per%20day%20for%20food%2C%20shelter%2C%20clothing%20and%20counselling.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20thing%20that%20happens%20when%20anyone%20enters%20this%20shelter%20is%20that%20they%20go%20through%20counselling%20by%20queer-affirmative%20mental%20health%20professionals%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%20The%20shelter%20does%20not%20currently%20provide%20de-addiction%20and%20psychosocial%20support.%20Queer%20persons%20at%20the%20shelter%20who%20are%20suffering%20from%20addiction%20are%20directed%20to%20reliable%20professionals%20who%20can%20provide%20that%20sort%20of%20care.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20Ya_All%20does%20not%20accept%20calls%20from%20parents%20who%20want%20to%20forcibly%20put%20their%20children%20in%20their%20centres.%20It%E2%80%99s%20imperative%20that%20the%20young%20and%20queer%20person%20in%20question%20gives%20their%20consent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%